# Node/edge parity rule (`GraphRAG_Project`)

When adding or changing a graph **node type** or **edge type**, keep parity with existing implemented types in the same change set.

## Required update checklist

- Update schema and contracts together (`src/graph/schema.py`, `src/schema_contract.py`, edge/node dataclasses).
- Update producers and resolvers together (extractors, `graph_builder`, serializer payload fields).
- Update analysis outputs so new types appear in in-degree/out-degree text sections where other types already appear.
- Update visualization outputs so new types have matching per-type charts/structure exports where applicable.
- Update UI schema explanations in compatibility/results templates so node and edge descriptions stay accurate.
- Update docs (`README.md`, `docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md`, and relevant feature docs) in the same PR.

## Consistency expectations

- Do not leave a new type only in extraction code while omitting analysis/visual/UI text updates.
- Do not mark implemented types as "future work" in templates/docs after code support lands.
- Keep naming consistent across code + UI + docs (same edge/node token and semantics).

## Verification before finishing

- Run the smallest relevant check (import smoke, pipeline run, or targeted script) that exercises the new type.
- Confirm generated artifacts and report text include the new type where peers are listed.
